        <deployment></deployment>
        <variants></variants>
        <notables>Sergeant Brinella MacKenna: When Sergeant Brinella MacKenna returned to Arc-Royal after raiding Zanderij, she was assigned a Lyran Hunchback IIC to replace her gutted Gauntlet. A Kell Hound couldn’t be picky in early September 3146, so she drowned her sorrow in a bottle of whiskey. The next morning, she was dragged out of bed to reports of five Clusters of Falcons landing on-world. Given the limitations of her ’Mech, MacKenna was assigned to defend Old Connaught. In the second week, the Fifty-Third Falcon Talon hit. Her lance managed to grind through a Star of light ’Mechs when a black and green Shrike descended upon them. Two of her companions died in seconds. Out-massed, out-gunned, and outmaneuvered, MacKenna grappled the Shrike, pinning it to the ground and firing shell after shell into it. When her LB 20-Xs ran dry she ejected and hoped for the best, not knowing she was leaving a deeply fuming Khan Malvina Hazen on the ground.</notables>
